review_blob: Very nice alternative to Guinness, definitely a fresher product. Very nice toffee notes, and creamy head.

Anchor Christmas 2012 (Our Special Ale) is the best I have had in 5-7 years.  The ale had hints of Juniper and Sasparilla, I love Anchors line of ales, they keep the classics consistent and have come out with some nice limited releases.
beer_name: Anchor Our Special Ale (2005 and later)

review_blob: Truly one of the best beers I have ever had, by far the best overall stout. Not to mention aged in Whiskey Barrels which gives me the best of both worlds Beer + Whiskey! The 2012 is a 15% ABV but you would never tell by the smooth taste!

Troegs has hit a homerun with Troegs Perpetual IPA (The First Imperial Pale Ale I have tried). Very nice balance of hops with a nice citra finish, obviously they are making great beers as noted by winning Best Mid Sized Brewery of The Year at the GABF!

Never really enjoyed Troegs Mad Elf, but the 2012 Mad Elf really has a nice balance of cherries, honey and spice. It was also great mixed with Troegs Dreamweaver Wheat, which was an option at Chaps Taproom in East Norriton, PA.
beer_name: Tregs The Mad Elf Holiday Ale

review_blob: Best Craft Dry Irish Stout in my opinion! Rich Chocolate Hue, milk like texture with hints of chocolate and vanilla.

You can barely taste the strawberry, which to me is a good thing. The jalapeno character comes through but not at all spicy. I adds more of an earthy/doughy character that works well with the brown ale style, but with a peppery aftertaste.

had on-tap at the Tex-Mex. Nice to see restaurant supporting local breweries. 

appears a darker copper amber color, with nice white head. The cap of head covers the beer until the very end.

aroma is pretty sweet, dominated by the honey. Taste follows similarly, with a fairly sweet flavors of malt and honey. The hops are subtle. Mouthfeel is very smooth, with lower carbonation that definitely works.
